An Act establishing the program of all-inclusive care for the elderly.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 118E of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition, is hereby
2 amended by inserting after section 9F the following section:-
3 Section 9G. (a) As used in this section, the following words shall have the following
4 meanings:-
5 “Capitation”, a set dollar payment per enrollee per month that the division pays to a
6 PACE organization to cover a specified set of services and administrative costs without regard to
7 the actual number of services provided.
8 ''Dually eligible'', any person, who is simultaneously qualified for full benefits under Title
9 XIX of the Social Security Act, 42 U.S.C 1396 et seq., and Title XVIII of the Social Security
10 Act, 42 U.S.C 1395 et seq.
1 of 6

11 ''Enrollee”, any dually eligible, MassHealth-only member or private pay individual, who
12 is voluntarily enrolled in a PACE program in accordance with the enrollment criteria as
13 established by MassHealth.
14 “Executive Office” is the Executive Office of Health and Human Services.
15 “Interdisciplinary Care Team (IDT)”, a group of health care and social service
16 professionals who assess needs, develop care plans, and deliver, monitor, and coordinate services
17 to PACE enrollees.
18 'MassHealth'', a program of full or partial medical benefits provided as authorized by this
19 chapter.
20 ''Medicare'', the federal health insurance program for elderly and disabled persons, and
21 persons with kidney failure established pursuant to Title XVIII of the Social Security Act, 42
22 U.S.C 1395 et seq.
23 “Program of All Inclusive Care for the Elderly (PACE)” a service delivery model
24 designed to keep older persons at risk of nursing facility placement in the community while
25 providing for medical and social long term care needs.
26 “PACE Organization” a MassHealth approved organization that provides comprehensive
27 healthcare services to PACE enrollees in accordance with a PACE Program Agreement as
28 described in 42USC 1396u-4.
29 “PACE Program” a program of all-inclusive care for the elderly that is operated by an
30 approved PACE organization and that provides comprehensive healthcare services to PACE
31 enrollees in accordance with a PACE program agreement.
2 of 6

32 “PACE Program Agreement” an agreement between a PACE organization, the Centers
33 for Medicaid and Medicare Services (CMS), and MassHealth, for the operation of a PACE
34 program in accordance with 42 USC 1396u-4.
35 (b) Notwithstanding any general or special law to the contrary, MassHealth, subject to
36 appropriation and the availability of federal financial participation, shall administer a program of
37 medical and long-term care benefits known as the Program of All Inclusive Care for the Elderly
38 (PACE), a comprehensive service delivery and financing model that uses interdisciplinary teams
39 in PACE Program day centers to assess and monitor the needs of enrollees and integrates
40 medical and long-term services and supports (LTSS), for Massachusetts residents who meet the
41 eligibility criteria in accordance with 42 CFR 460.150.
42 (c) Enrollees in PACE shall meet MassHealth's skilled-nursing-facility level of care
43 criteria, reside in a PACE service area, determined by the Social Security Administration to need
44 the level of care required under the State Medicaid plan for coverage of nursing facility services,
45 and are able to live in a community setting without jeopardizing their health or safety.
46 (d) MassHealth will contract with entities known as PACE organizations to provide a
47 comprehensive network of medical, health care and social services that integrate all components
48 of care, either directly or through subcontracts, and is provided in day-health centers, at home,
49 and in specialty or inpatient settings.
50 (e) MassHealth shall ensure that enrollment in the program is voluntary. To the extent
51 consistent with federal law and regulations, MassHealth shall ensure that all enrollees in a PACE
52 program have the right to disenroll from the program in any month upon submitting a notice of
53 disenrollment to the division or contracted entity. Disenrollment notices received by the division
3 of 6

54 or contracted entity by the twentieth day of the month shall be effective the first day of the
55 following month.
56 (f) The benefits provided enrollees in PACE, pursuant to 42 CFR 460.92 1396u-4(f),
57 shall include those services covered by Medicare Part A and Part B; the amount, duration and
58 scope of Medicaid-covered services shall be at a minimum no more restrictive than the scope of
59 services provided under MassHealth standard coverage; and services necessary for the treatment
60 of mental health and substance abuse.
61 (g) MassHealth shall educate consumers and their families as to their enrollment choices
62 under MassHealth and other available alternatives under Medicare and Medicaid. Neither PACE
63 organizations nor MassHealth shall offer gifts, payments or other inducements to enroll seniors
64 in PACE. MassHealth shall also perform outreach services to local councils on aging, Aging
65 Services Access Points (ASAPs) and other related organizations to educate those councils and
66 organizations on the details of PACE, including, but not limited to, providing the councils and
67 organizations with the PACE educational materials listed in subsection (h).
68 (h) MassHealth shall deliver to all prospective PACE enrollees educational materials that
69 shall include, but not be limited to: a definition of PACE and how it functions; enrollment
70 eligibility standards; the location of PACE programs; a complete list of their participating
71 providers; the range of available services; consumer rights under Medicare and Medicaid; an
72 assistance worksheet for determining health care options under MassHealth and Medicare; Long
73 Term Care Ombudsman contact information; and the process for an applicant to appeal a
74 negative eligibility decision.
